The paper deals with image restoration using wavelet frame systems, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of sparsity and nonlocal priors also suggests that the paper could belong to information theory (cs.IT) or signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and optimization, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
